## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="84ca4-157"><xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient> está pensado para que se crea una instancia y volver a usar durante la vida de una aplicación.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="84ca4-157"><xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient> is intended to be instantiated once and re-used throughout the life of an application.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="84ca4-158">Crear una instancia de una clase HttpClient para cada solicitud agotará al número de sockets disponibles con cargas pesadas.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="84ca4-158">Instantiating an HttpClient class for every request will exhaust the number of sockets available under heavy loads.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="84ca4-159">Esto provocará errores SocketException.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="84ca4-159">This will result in SocketException errors.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="84ca4-160">A continuación es un ejemplo de uso de HttpClient correctamente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="84ca4-160">Below is an example using HttpClient correctly.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public class GoodController : ApiController  
{  
    // OK  
    private static readonly HttpClient HttpClient;  
  
    static GoodController()  
    {  
        HttpClient = new HttpClient();  
    }  
}  
  
```
